omething.";i:15;s:74:"The songs I choose have inspirational lyrics or are just fun and familiar.";i:16;s:173:"Researchers examined the effects of chair yoga on physical function including balance and mobility and compared the effects with chair-based exercise and music intervention.";i:17;s:187:"They also looked at the effects of chair yoga on reducing psychological symptoms like anxiety and depression behavioral symptoms like agitation or aggression and improved quality of life.";i:18;s:193:"Chair yoga more effective than music therapy in older adults with advanced dementia Pilot study first to show adults with advanced dementia can participate in non-pharmacological interventions.";i:19;s:162:"Chair Yoga is approved by the Arthritis Foundation to ease the aches and pains of arthritis sufferers and is very beneficial for people with sedentary lifestyles.";i:20;s:171:"Chair Yoga Benefits Increases circulation Range of motion movements in the feet legs knees hips shoulders and elbows help the general well-being and function of the heart.";i:21;s:193:"Chair yoga more effective than music therapy in older adults with advanced dementia Pilot study first to show adults with advanced dementia can participate in non-pharmacological interventions.";i:22;s:120:"According to Yogapedia almost any traditional yoga pose or move can be replicated and altered to accommodate chair yoga.";i:23;s:261:"Along with increased ranges of motion through holding poses on a chair pranayamas also known as breathing techniques are a popular practice within chair yoga and can assist in reducing anxiety introducing or practicing meditation and creating spatial awareness.";i:24;s:95:"Healing Yoga - Path of Deep Reflections Inner Exploration Stress Relief Mind and Body Practice.";i:25;s:65:"Life with Yoga - Ambient Music for Best Yoga Poses Practice 2021.";i:26;s:42:"Relaxing Yoga Music for Kids and Children.";i:27;s:23:"Chair Yoga for Seniors.";i:28;s:44:"Yoga for Anxiety Meditation Focus Calm Down.";i:29;s:103:"We found a fantastic 30 minute routine of gentle chair yoga for seniors thats free to watch on YouTube.";i:30;s:103:"Instructor Sherry Zak Morris makes the class fun and lively and explains the benefits of the movements.";i:31;s:131:"We share customization and safety tips and give an overview of the movements included in this 30 minute at-home chair yoga routine.";i:32;s:129:"In this chair-assisted yoga practice Erica integrates yoga postures and gentle strengthening techniques for a total body workout.";i:33;s:152:"The class may be suitable for students with limited mobility but there are several standing postures some of which can be modified in a seated position.";i:34;s:24:"This is a Level 2 class.";i:35;s:115:"Chair Yoga invites you to find mobility in a way that is soft and gentle but also really supportive and beneficial.";i:36;s:102:"This 17 min practice invites awareness and integrity into the body specifically the line of the spine.";i:37;s:103:"Activate the muscles that help you find length up through the spine for better posture and energy flow.";i:38;s:117:"As a yoga instructor you want to be able to offer clientele safe and fun modifications compared to traditional poses.";i:39;s:105:"This course will give you three full-length chair yoga practices as well as a breakdown of 30 yoga poses.";i:40;s:55:"Its a great course for anyone looking to teach yoga to.";i:41;s:145:"Listen to Chair Yoga - Chair Yoga Poses at Work to Reduce Stress Yoga Music for a Clear Mind and a Balanced Body by Yoga Waheguru on Apple Music.";i:42;s:46:"Chair Yoga with Nadia Narain - Chair Practice.";i:43;s:60:"Chair Yoga with Nadia Narain - Seated and Standing Practice.";i:44;s:43:"Chair Yoga with Nadia Narain - Ground Flow.";i:45;s:120:"Below is a list of basic chair yoga poses which are ancient yoga poses that have been adapted to practice using a chair.";i:46;s:149:"These chair yoga poses could be used in your classroom homeschool or in a small space for transitions movement breaks or for introducing a new topic.";i:47;s:89:"The postures serve as an inspiration guide but please encourage the childrens creativity.";i:48;s:161:"I jumped right in with an offering of chair yoga asking for the group to be kept small at no more than 14 or 16 people and hoping that at least 10 would show up.";i:49;s:167:"One of the music rooms was made available for the session and I set it up with 18 chairs facing the window and the many plants see photo below with the initial set up.";i:50;s:47:"6 chair exercises in an easy 10 minute routine.";i:51;s:126:"Dartmouth-Hitchcock an East Coast health care organization created a simple 10 minute chair exercise routine for older adults.";i:52;s:123:"The only equipment thats needed is a sturdy chair with back support an optional resistance band and optional ankle weights.";i:53;s:29:"The chair shouldnt have arms.";}}